HEADWORD: Amandine
<hw>A*man"dine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>amande</ets> almond. See <er>Almond</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The vegetable casein of almonds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of cold cream prepared from almonds, for
chapped hands, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amanita</ent>⟦br⟧
